article.headline: Gardner-Webb 60, High Point 57
article.story: HIGH POINT, N.C. -- Grayson Flittner hit a 3-pointer with 27 seconds remaining to help Gardner-Webb defeat High Point 60-57 on Saturday night. High Point led 57-56 when Flittner hit the 3-pointer for Gardner-Webb's first lead since 3:32 left in the game. Flittner, who finished with 20 points, added a free throw with 2 seconds left to help seal the victory. Aaron Linn also scored 20 points for Gardner-Webb (6-9, 2-3 Big South Conference). High Point (5-10, 1-4) tied the score at 54-54 on David Singleton's layup with 2:33 remaining in the game. Singleton hit a free throw and Cruz Daniels scored for a 57-54 advantage with 1:32 left. But Gardner-Webb's Nate Blank hit a jumper with 1:10 remaining, setting up Flittner's shot. Singleton led High Point with 18 points, Daniels had 15 points and 11 rebounds and Eugene Harris added 13 points.
